products.manufacturer: GOODYEAR DUNLOP TIRES NORTH AMERICA, LTD

summary: DRIVING MY HARLEY ELECTRA GLIDE CLASSIC DOWN I-90 IN SOUTH DAKOTA AT AROUND 80 MPH MY BIKE STARTED  TO SWAY FROM FRONT TO BACK.  I THOUGHT IT WAS THE ROAD AT FIRST, SINCE IT WAS A ROAD WITH LINES, WITH SUCK FOR BIKES.  IT STARTED GETTING WORSE SO I SLOWED AND PULLED OVER.  FLAT REAR TIRE.  D402 FROM DUNLOP..  I FEEL GLAD TO BE ALIVE.  I HAD THE TIRE REPLACED.  THE MECHANIC DID NOT FIND ANYTHING IN THE TIRE, BUT THE LEFT SIDE WAS ALL BUBBLED.  HE SAID THERE WAS NO WAY OF KNOWING IF IT CAUSED THE FLAT OR WAS THE RESULT OF THE FLAT. *TR

TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2005 HARLEY DAVIDSON FLHTC.  WHILE DRIVING 65 MPH, THE CONTACT HEARD A NOISE COMING FROM THE REAR OF THE VEHICLE.  HE NOTICED THAT THE PIPE THAT HOLDS THE TOUR PACK HAD SEVERED, WHICH WEDGED THE TOUR PACK BEHIND THE LICENSE.  THE DEALER STATED THAT THIS WAS A KNOWN FAILURE AND ADVISED THE CONTACT TO SPEAK WITH THE MANUFACTURER.  THE MANUFACTURER STATED THAT NOTHING COULD BE DONE.  THE VIN WAS UNKNOWN.  THE CURRENT MILEAGE IS 26,000 AND FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 25,000.
CONSUMER 2005 HARLEY DAVIDSON FRONT RIGHT OF THE FRAME HAS EXPOSED METAL.  *TS  (11/16/05)  THE COATING WAS CHIPPING NEAR AND ON THE WELD EXPOSING THE BARE METAL WHICH WAS SLIGHTLY RUSTED.  *SC
